
<h4 style="color:#72A0C1; font-family:verdana; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 200;">Innodb Buffer pool</h4>
<p style="font-family:Arial; font-size: 13px;">
The InnoDB buffer pool should generally be set to 60-80% of the available RAM when using InnoDB exclusively. Ideally, all InnoDB data and indexes should be able to fit within memory. 
</p>
<p style="font-family:Arial; font-size: 13px;">
A high value of the InnoDB Buffer Pool cache hit ratio suggests mariadb is able to efficiently handle page reads from the Buffer Pool. A low value would suggest otherwise â€“ Inadequately sized Buffer Pool, etc.
</p>
<p style="font-family:Arial; font-size: 13px;">
A high value (>1)  of InnoDB Waits for Checkpoint will suggest an inadequately sized Buffer Pool, and database operations had to wait on a checkpoint to take place.
</p>

